####jitter plots for all groups (incl 1-male days) w/ linear regression lines####

###For Loop for Avg. # of Males Across Months for all Groups####
par(mfrow=c(3,3))
df_groups=list(gn_10yrs,gs_10yrs,gsa,gsaa,gsb,gsc,tw_10yrs,tws,twn)
mainlabel=c("Gn Avg. Male Group Size Per Month","Gs Avg. Male Group Size Per Month","Gsa Avg. Male Group Size Per Month","Gsaa Avg. Male Group Size Per Month","Gsb Avg. Male Group Size Per Month","Gsc Avg. Male Group Size Per Month","Tw Avg. Male Group Size Per Month","Tws Avg. Male Group Size Per Month","Twn Avg. Male Group Size Per Month")

#df_groups=list(tws,twn)
#mainlabel=c("Tws","Twn")

for(i in c(1:9)){

  z=df_groups[[i]]
  #frame()
  agg = aggregate(z, by = list(match(months(z$Date), month.name)), mean)
  males = agg$Male.Group.Size
  females = agg$Female.Group.Size
  dates <- seq(as.Date(min(z$Date), format = "%d/%m/%Y"),by = "months", length = length(agg$Date))
  max.y<-ceiling(max(males))
  plot(dates,males, col = "blue", type="b",lty=3,pch=20,xlab = "Month", cex.lab=1.5,xaxt = "n",ylab="Avg. Group Size",main=mainlabel[i],ylim=c(0,max.y),cex.main=.75,cex.axis=.75,cex.lab=.75)
  axis(side = 1, at = dates, labels = month.abb, cex.axis = 0.7,tck=-.05)
  }

###For Loop for Avg. # of Females Across Months for all Groups####
par(mfrow=c(3,3))
df_groups=list(gn_10yrs,gs_10yrs,gsa,gsaa,gsb,gsc,tw_10yrs,tws,twn)
mainlabel=c("Gn Avg. Female Group Size Per Month","Gs Avg. Female Group Size Per Month","Gsa Avg. Female Group Size Per Month","Gsaa Avg. Female Group Size Per Month","Gsb Avg. Female Group Size Per Month","Gsc Avg. Female Group Size Per Month","Tw Avg. Female Group Size Per Month","Tws Avg. Female Group Size Per Month","Twn Avg. Female Group Size Per Month")

#df_groups=list(tws,twn)
#mainlabel=c("Tws","Twn")

for(i in c(1:9)){

  z=df_groups[[i]]
  #frame()
  agg = aggregate(z, by = list(match(months(z$Date), month.name)), mean)
  males = agg$Male.Group.Size
  females = agg$Female.Group.Size
  dates <- seq(as.Date(min(z$Date), format = "%d/%m/%Y"),by = "months", length = length(agg$Date))
  max.y<-ceiling(max(females))
  plot(dates,females, col = "red", type="b",lty=3,pch=20,xlab = "Month", cex.lab=1.5,xaxt = "n",ylab="Avg. Group Size",main=mainlabel[i],ylim=c(0,max.y),cex.main=.75,cex.axis=.75,cex.lab=.75)
  axis(side = 1, at = dates, labels = month.abb, cex.axis = 0.7,tck=-.05)
  }
